---
methods:
  composeShowcase: |
    const headings = vm.report.getHeadings();
    const pageCount = vm.report.getPageCount();
    const summaryText = `This panel was inserted after settlement. It discovered ${headings.length} headings across ${pageCount} settled page${pageCount === 1 ? '' : 's'} and then requested one replay to become part of the real document flow.`;
    const previewEntries = headings.map((heading, index) => ({
      type: 'p',
      content: `${index + 1}. ${heading.heading} - page ${heading.pageIndex + 1}`,
      properties: {
        sourceId: `navigation-preview-entry-${index + 1}`,
        semanticRole: 'navigation-preview-entry',
        style: {
          marginBottom: 6,
          paddingLeft: 8,
          borderLeftWidth: 3,
          borderLeftColor: '#c8a96a'
        }
      }
    }));
    const panelMissing = !vm.doc.get('showcase-panel-title');
    const currentSummary = vm.doc.get('showcase-panel-summary');
    const currentPreviewTitle = vm.doc.get('navigation-preview-title');
    const currentPreviewEntries = vm.doc.findByRole('navigation-preview-entry');
    const summaryChanged = !currentSummary || String(currentSummary.content || '') !== summaryText;
    const previewChanged =
      !currentPreviewTitle ||
      currentPreviewEntries.length !== previewEntries.length ||
      currentPreviewEntries.some((entry, index) => String(entry.content || '') !== previewEntries[index].content);
    if (!panelMissing && !summaryChanged && !previewChanged) return;
    if (panelMissing) vm.doc.insertAfter('showcase-title', [
      {
        type: 'p',
        content: 'SCRIPTED DOCUMENT',
        properties: {
          sourceId: 'showcase-panel-kicker',
          semanticRole: 'showcase-panel-kicker',
          style: {
            marginBottom: 6,
            fontWeight: 700,
            letterSpacing: 1.2,
            color: '#8b5e34'
          }
        }
      },
      {
        type: 'h1',
        content: 'Runtime Synopsis',
        properties: {
          sourceId: 'showcase-panel-title',
          semanticRole: 'showcase-panel-title',
          style: {
            marginBottom: 10,
            color: '#183153'
          }
        }
      },
      {
        type: 'p',
        content: summaryText,
        properties: {
          sourceId: 'showcase-panel-summary',
          semanticRole: 'showcase-panel-summary',
          style: {
            marginBottom: 14,
            paddingTop: 10,
            paddingBottom: 10,
            paddingLeft: 12,
            paddingRight: 12,
            backgroundColor: '#f5efe6',
            borderWidth: 1,
            borderColor: '#d8c3a8'
          }
        }
      }
    ]);
    if (!panelMissing && summaryChanged) vm.doc.setContent('showcase-panel-summary', summaryText);
    if (previewChanged) {
      vm.doc.remove('navigation-preview-anchor');
      vm.doc.remove('navigation-preview-title');
      vm.doc.findByRole('navigation-preview-entry').forEach((entry) => {
        const sourceId = entry && entry.properties ? entry.properties.sourceId : null;
        if (typeof sourceId === 'string' && sourceId) vm.doc.remove(sourceId);
      });
      vm.doc.insertBefore('act-1', [
        {
          type: 'h1',
          content: 'Navigation Preview',
          properties: {
            sourceId: 'navigation-preview-title',
            semanticRole: 'navigation-preview-title',
            style: {
              marginTop: 12,
              marginBottom: 10,
              color: '#183153'
            }
          }
        },
        ...previewEntries
      ]);
    }
    vm.requestReplay();
---
{
  "documentVersion": "1.1",
  "layout": {
    "pageSize": { "width": 380, "height": 320 },
    "margins": { "top": 28, "right": 28, "bottom": 28, "left": 28 },
    "fontFamily": "Arimo",
    "fontSize": 12,
    "lineHeight": 1.28
  },
  "fonts": {
    "regular": "Arimo"
  },
  "styles": {
    "p": { "marginBottom": 10, "allowLineSplit": true, "orphans": 2, "widows": 2, "color": "#202833" },
    "h1": { "fontSize": 20, "fontWeight": "bold", "marginTop": 0, "marginBottom": 12, "keepWithNext": true, "color": "#101c2c" }
  },
  "onAfterSettle": "composeShowcase",
  "elements": [
    {
      "type": "h1",
      "content": "Scripting Showcase",
      "properties": {
        "sourceId": "showcase-title",
        "semanticRole": "showcase-title"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "This document is intentionally authored as ordinary AST content first. The scripting layer then augments it after settlement, proving the runtime can participate in composition without turning the AST into an embedded scripting language."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "The authored structure includes a placeholder region lower in the document for a generated navigation preview. The rest of the document remains perfectly static and readable even before scripting runs."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Pending navigation preview",
      "properties": {
        "sourceId": "navigation-preview-anchor"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "h1",
      "content": "Act I: The Prompt",
      "properties": {
        "sourceId": "act-1",
        "semanticRole": "h1"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "A long opening section gives the layout engine enough material to produce a meaningful settlement. It also ensures that the generated panel and preview are not trivial one-line substitutions, but part of a larger and more realistic flow. The narrative keeps going, explaining how a document system becomes more approachable the moment it can be observed, scripted, and reshaped from within its own runtime."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "More body text continues the first act. The point is less the words themselves than the fact that there is enough authored material for the script to discover a real outline and settled pagination. That is the thing we want developers to see: the runtime is not only rendering text, it is exposing just enough of its own world state to become programmable."
    },
    {
      "type": "h1",
      "content": "Act II: The Replay",
      "properties": {
        "sourceId": "act-2",
        "semanticRole": "h1"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "The second act exists to prove the replay loop is doing something useful. After settlement, the script inserts a synopsis panel near the title, replaces the preview placeholder with generated entries, and then asks the engine for one fresh pass so the resulting document is laid out as though it had always existed in that shape."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "That fresh pass is what makes the system interesting. The script is not merely an afterthought painting on top of finished pages. It is participating in composition, yet it still returns ordinary AST. This is exactly the middle ground we have been looking for."
    },
    {
      "type": "h1",
      "content": "Act III: The Invitation",
      "properties": {
        "sourceId": "act-3",
        "semanticRole": "h1"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "The third act is the invitation to developers. Once they see this document rebuild itself through a small script, they can imagine title pages, outlines, report summaries, running matter, and eventually a real table of contents. The feature is not the panel itself. The feature is the door it opens."
    }
  ]
}
